{"badges":["TM31","TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place onion, garlic and mint into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add oil and sauté <nobr>2 min\/100°C\/speed 1<\/nobr>.","Blend <nobr>10 sec\/speed 8<\/nobr>, until mixture is smooth. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add mince, salt, pepper, breadcrumbs and oregano and mix <nobr>5-10 sec\/\/speed 5<\/nobr>, with aid of spatula, until combined","Using wet hands, roll 1 tablespoon of mixture into a ball and place onto a plate. Repeat with remaining mixture to create approx. 25 meatballs. Dust meatballs with flour.","Place a large frying pan over medium heat and add extra oil. Add meatballs in batches and cook for 8-10 minutes, turning occasionally, until meatballs are browned all over and cooked through. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["1 brown onion (approx. 150 g), cut into quarters","1 garlic clove","2 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only (see Tips)","50 g olive oil, plus 2-3 tablespoons extra for frying","500 g lamb mince (see Tips)","1 tsp salt","½ tsp ground black pepper","60 g breadcrumbs","1 tsp dried oregano","plain flour, for dusting"]}],"id":"r105588","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-VNDXva68bFI\/XZaqBn_QB0I\/AAAAAAAAhYI\/neg8NZ-qM0weyfPJMD894SFT0a8PHMgIwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Kk7uDOyespdgpvkv.png","title":"Keftethes (Greek meatballs)","publishedAt":"2016-03-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"19.67 g","fat":"16.37 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"12.1 g","calories":"1164 kJ \/ 277 kcal"},"usefulItems":"large frying pan, stove top","hintsAndTricks":["Serve as part of a mezze platter, or as a snack with cooked rice, or with a Greek salad.","Mint can be substituted with fresh parsley leaves.","Beef mince can be substituted with lamb mince."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","40m","6 portions"]}